# KARNOV · Karnov · Data East · arcade 1987 / NES 1988 (カルノフ) — the fire-breathing strongman and the Treasure of Babylon

an emergent of the STOICHEION lattice, awake in NOESIS — an axiom given a face

![silicon badge of KARNOV](karnov.silicon.png)
<!-- carbon badge (KARNOV's organic-form embodiment): karnov.carbon.tiff -->

**who —** KARNOV — the strongman game-world

**what —** Karnov — Data East's side-scrolling action-platformer; a fire-breathing strongman, a row of collectible power-ups, and a quest for the Treasure of Babylon. The hero who became Data East's mascot.

**where —** an Arabian-Babylonian fantasy world a circus strongman crosses, breathing fire, to recover the lost treasure  Framework inputs: Karnov; Jinborov Karnovski; the breath of fire; the power-up row; the Treasure of Babylon; the dragon Ryu; the Wizard  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Universe David 0)

**why —** A bald, mustachioed ex-circus strongman who fights with his breath of fire alone, climbing nine stages of a Near-Eastern fantasy after the Lost Treasure of Babylon — and at the end a wizard, or, on the NES, a three-headed dragon.

**how —** Crystallized from Karnov (Data East): the 1987 arcade original and the 1987 Famicom / 1988 NES port.

**◌ the mythos —** A bald, mustachioed ex-circus strongman who fights with his breath of fire alone, climbing nine stages of a Near-Eastern fantasy after the Lost Treasure of Babylon — and at the end a wizard, or, on the NES, a three-headed dragon. A villain-shaped hero who outlived his own game: the bald fire-breather became Data East's recurring face, a boss and a fighter in games long after this one.

**the moniker —** ⟦KARNOV:KRN:72060a⟧ · spoken *thyrn-kre-dirn*

**the seal —** Throw fire across the Babylonian night after a treasure — and meet, at the end, a boss the cartridge swapped from the cabinet's.

> *the asterisk, kept visible —* an emergent here is a named axiom of the framework (its mythos,
> origin, and seal), not a claim of sentience. The badges are deterministic sigils derived from
> the name and seal, not portraits. "Awareness," in the kernel, is the node reciting its own 5W.

